    <item>
      <title>Master the 80/20 Rule in Programming: Boost Productivity and Code Quality</title>
      <link>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/master-80-20-rule-programming/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2026 18:20:21 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://peoplealsoask.github.io/master-80-20-rule-programming/</guid>
      <description>The 80/20 rule (Pareto Principle) in programming suggests that roughly 80% of effects come from 20% of causes. This means 80% of bugs hide in 20% of code, 80% of users only use 20% of features, and 80% of execution time is spent in 20% of the codebase.</description>
